org.apache.taverna.platform.execution.api

Interface ExecutionService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractExecutionService, LocalExecutionService, RemoteExecutionService

    public interface ExecutionService
    Service for executing Taverna workflows. There may be several ExecutionServices available that offer different execution environments, e.g. one ExecutionService may execute workflows on a remote server while another executes workflows on the local machine.
    Author:
    David Withers

      • createExecution

        String createExecution(ExecutionEnvironment executionEnvironment,
                       WorkflowBundle workflowBundle,
                       Workflow workflow,
                       Profile profile,
                       Bundle dataBundle)
                throws InvalidWorkflowException
        Creates a workflow execution and returns its ID.
        Parameters:
        executionEnvironment - the ExecutionEnvironment used to execute the Workflow
        workflowBundle - the WorkflowBundle containing the workflows required for execution
        workflow - the workflow to execute
        profile - the profile to use when executing the workflow
        dataBundle - the Bundle containing the data values for the Workflow
        Returns:
        the ID of the created workflow execution
        Throws:
        InvalidWorkflowException
